column8: Description / Notes

TriOS sensor and data logger were configured to allow data to be uploaded to the data server. It was also discovered that the suction hose and buoy had been pulled ashore by mistake. During the swim, it was installed back in its more or less normal position.

A heat cable and insulation were installed around the suction pipe to prevent freezing in the winter. In addition, the heat cable also runs through other parts of the system to ensure that the system also functions in the winter.
The Coliminder PCB was replaced and an attempt was made to fix the TriOS sensor through configuration, as it was giving unreadable outputs.
Sensor configuration was performed on the TriOS sensor to get its results readable but was not resultative.
Sensor configuration was performed on the TriOS sensor to get its results readable but was not resultative.
By the temperature data and visit on site it was figured out that inflow pump was not working during that period.
Coliminder unstable values
Sensor configuration was performed on the TriOS sensor to get its results readable but was not resultative. The EXO sensor was reviewed.

The buffer tank was cleaned after 1.5 months of operation, a noticeable layer of sediment had formed. The buffer tank was cleaned and an elbow fitting was added to the inlet of the buffer tank to fit two 35L tanks (Di-water and Coliminder waste) next to it.
Reagent exchange was performed on the Coliminder. This includes exchange of reagent A, B and washing solution topping-up.
Sensor configuration was performed on the TriOS sensor to get its results readable but was not resultative.

Added local computer to control data logger remotely, extra Ethernet switch and other additions were needed to make that possible. Added remote control and monitoring for heating cable. Emptied Coliminder waste tank and filled Di-water tank. Added local signalisation for extra safety.
Changed TriOS sensor communication from Modbus to 4-20 mA and it started working.
Checked if everything runs correctly and cleaned TriOS sensor optical glass.
Check
DI-water refill+moving buoy+removed biofilm from suction pump inlet screen.
DI-water refill

Reagent exchange was performed on the Coliminder. This includes exchange of reagent A, B and washing solution topping-up. We also controlled TriOS sensor in DI-water before and after cleaning the optical screen.
DI-water refill!
Colimidner reagent change!
